entry.title: Don't remap lightness for oklab/oklch
entry.content:
lab/lch have lightness in the range [0,100] (which unfortunately

equals [0%,100%] in this instance, oh well) while oklab/oklch use

lightness in the range [0,1]. We were storing lightness for all four

color spaces in the range [0,100], which increased complexity and

broke behavior for calc functions in RCS (see added tests).



This CL changes blink::Color so that it stores lightness for oklab/

oklch in the range [0,1]. It also includes changes for unit tests that

had to previously interact with oklab/oklch colors _as if_ they have

entry.title: Add SessionId member to FormDataAndroid.
entry.content:
Android Autofill identifies form fields by their virtual ids. These

are generated from two components:

- A 16 bit session id that is unique to the Autofill session.

- The index of the field the user interacted with inside the form.



Currently these are generated inside AutofillRequest.java with a simple

logic: The session id is a static counter that counts up by one whenever

a new request is created.



In the future, we may wish for multiple requests to have the same id in

order to identify form's for which a prefill request has been sent with

forms for which an actual session was started. This means that we will

need some more control over session ids - preferably on the C++ side.



This CL is the first of two to migrate the logic of creating session ids

from Java to C++. It adds a SessionId member to FormDataAndroid and

a generation function for SessionIds to AutofillProviderAndroid.

A follow-up CL will use this SessionId on the Java side.

entry.title: [blink] Remove check for IsLost() when CanvasResource destroys resources
entry.content:
We want to be guaranteed that the destruction of the SharedImage here is

actually occurring via this call. At present, the check for IsLost() is

the only meaningful thing preventing that (the other checks are that

either the entire SII was already torn down or that the SharedImage was

never successfully created in the first place). This check was added as

part of a speculative fix for a ClusterFuzz bug (crbug.com/1433545). The

same CL added the check for IsValid(), which is what actually fixed the

bug. IsLost() doesn't mean that the resource shouldn't be destroyed, but

rather just that it shouldn't be reused.

entry.title: [android][selection] Update Paste as Plain Text Positioning
entry.content:
The Chrome UX team requested that the "Paste as plain text" menu item be

positioned next to "Paste". However, because we depend on the iterator of the menu group items for ordering, the menu group item collection

needs to be updated to use an implementation of `SortedSet` as opposed

to `PriorityQueue`. This is because `PriorityQueue`s iterator does not

guarantee any particular order.



See: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/PriorityQueue.html#iterator--

entry.title: QuickStart: Use Base64 type for FIDO credential id
entry.content:
Use Base64 as the type of FIDO credential id instead of std::string.

This will help us prevent encoding bugs. It is impossible to guess the

encoding of a std::string data, and can lead to double-encoding or

no-encoding bugs.



Additionally, use Base64 instead of Base64Url as the underlying encoding

(see https://crrev.com/c/5013510). This follows the encoding guideline

at https://protobuf.dev/programming-guides/proto3/#json. GoogleFE /

OnePlatform is lenient in allowing Base64Url representation of byte

array proto fields, but the canonical representation is still Base64

(not Base64Url).

entry.title: [//ash] Allow UiResource to take in ClientSharedImage
entry.content:
UiResource has two modes of operation with respect to the SharedImage

that it holds a reference to:



1. It owns the SharedImage and is responsible for calling

DestroySharedImage()

2. It does *not* own the SharedImage and should not call

DestroySharedImage()



This CL separates out these two cases explicitly by having UiResource

take in a scoped_refptr in the first case and

a gpu::Mailbox in the second case. This will allow clients of UiResource

that will need to access its ClientSharedImage to do so in followup

work (e.g., for converting MapSharedImage() from taking in a Mailbox to

taking in a ClientSharedImage).



Note that it is not viable to pass in ClientSharedImage in case 2:

- FastInkHost will call DestroySharedImage() on the ClientSI

- DestroySharedImage() CHECKs that there is only one reference on the

passed-in ClientSI

- The UiResources outlive FastInkHost, as they are destroyed in its

base class destructor



This CL also changes UiResource to call DestroySharedImage(ClientSI)

rather than DestroySharedImage(Mailbox) in the case where it is holding

a ClientSharedImage. This change is guaranteed to be safe as UiResource

does not give out its `client_si_`, so that ivar is guaranteed to be the

only reference to the ClientSharedImage.

entry.content:
In a previous CL I introduced field_by_field_filling_type_used to log

the field-by-field filling type. I initially added in the children

suggestion only, this CL also adds to the top level suggestion when its

type id field-by-field-filling.



However please note that we are not going to log the field type for

top level suggestions (first popup), at least not for now.

This is because the purpose of this log is to understand whether the

field by field fillling options we add to the children suggestions

are useful to the user. At the same time, the top level one is based

on the triggering field and is not something decided by granular

filling.



For the sake of consistent I am however also including the field type

used for top level suggestions. We might still in the future want to

log that, however it would certainly be a different metric or bucket.
